subSubSection.paragraph:
Female (
Fig. 1B
), similar to males, but usually larger. Ventrite VIII (
Fig. 2H
) slightly split medially at posterior margin and covered with long dense hair. Spiculum (
Fig. 2H
) tortuous at middle, apex rounded and slightly dilated. Apex of ovipositor (
Fig. 2I
) with one long hair and two much shorter hairs.
